push_ptn_network arguments: -help

Usage: push_ptn_network [-help] [-exclude_ptn_list <string>] [-filter <string>]
                        [-inst_prefix <string>] [-logical_only]
                        [-net_prefix <string>]
                        [-output_logical_only_nets <string>]
                        [-output_nets_for_wire_distribution <string>]
                        [-ptn_net_dir <string>] { -nets <string> | -file <string> | -buf_only | -insts <string> } [-check_only [-output <string>]]

-help                                  # Prints out the command usage
-buf_only                              # all placed buffers, and their
                                       # connected nets, will be considered for
                                       # pushed down (bool, required)
-check_only                            # simply inform which nets are going to
                                       # be pushed down (bool, optional)
-exclude_ptn_list <string>             # list of partition name(s) which are
                                       # excluded from push down of
                                       # instances/nets (string, optional)
-file <string>                         # file containing list of net names to
                                       # be considered for pushed down
                                       # (string, required)
-filter <string>                       # only instances/nets whose name matches
                                       # this specified regular expression will
                                       # be pushed down (string, optional)
-inst_prefix <string>                  # specifies a custom prefix for
                                       # instances that are pushed down
                                       # (string, optional)
-insts <string>                        # all placed instances, and their
                                       # connected nets, will be considered for
                                       # pushed down (string, required)
-logical_only                          # logically pushes down network into
                                       # overlapping partitions (bool, optional)
-net_prefix <string>                   # specifies a custom prefix for nets
                                       # that are pushed down (string, optional)
-nets <string>                         # list of net names, and their connected
                                       # instances, will be considered for
                                       # pushed down (string, required)
-output <string>                       # file name in which net names, to be
                                       # pushded down, will be mentioned; to be
                                       # used with -check_only (string, optional)
-output_logical_only_nets <string>     # file name containing net names; to be
                                       # used with -logical_only
                                       # (string, optional)
-output_nets_for_wire_distribution <string>
                                       # output the user specified nets, so
                                       # that they can be used later during
                                       # partition command (string, optional)
-ptn_net_dir <string>                  # directory in which net names
                                       # corresponding net names in each
                                       # partition, will be mentioned
                                       # (string, optional)